│ shuffle that feeds two matching operations (binops or cmps) into performing   │
│ the operations after shuffling the operands.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe  │
│ debug log indicates foldShuffleOfBinops fired on the shuffle of the two       │
│ icmps:\n  Found a shuffle feeding two binops: %res = shufflevector ...\nEven  │
│ though the log message says \"binops\", this function also handles compares.  │
│ Then it proceeds to erase the shuffle and both icmps, leaving a               │
│ zeroinitializer return.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nInspection of             │
│ foldShuffleOfBinops shows a clear type construction bug in the compare-cost   │
│ computation path:\n  auto *ShuffleCmpTy =                                     │
│ FixedVectorType::get(BinOpTy->getElementType(),                               │
│ ShuffleDstTy);\nFixedVectorType::get expects a scalar element type and a      │
│ number-of-elements (unsigned), but the code passes a type (ShuffleDstTy) in   │
│ the second argument. This is a silent, invalid API usage that can cause wrong │
│ cost modeling or undefined behavior via overload resolution, potentially      │
│ leading to miscomputed NewCost. Consequently, the profitability check can     │
│ become incorrect, allowing an illegal or semantically-changing transform to   │
│ proceed. As seen, the pass decides to fold and replaces the original sequence │
│ with a new compare and then erases the original instructions, ultimately      │
│ producing a constant zero result.\nThis is consistent with the log: the       │
│ transform was considered profitable and applied. While there may be a         │
│ separate issue around handling icmp samesign, the immediate, concrete defect  │
│ here is the wrong construction of the vector type used in getCmpSelInstrCost. │
│ That miscomputes costs and can cause the pass to trigger when it should not,  │
│ leading to the incorrect transformation.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n-     │
│ File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp\n  Lines: 1734-1736\n   │
│ Change:\n    auto *ShuffleCmpTy =\n                                           │
│ FixedVectorType::get(BinOpTy->getElementType(), ShuffleDstTy);\n  To:\n       │
│ auto *ShuffleCmpTy =\n        FixedVectorType::get(BinOpTy->getElementType(), │
│ ShuffleDstTy->getNumElements());\n\nReasoning:\nFixedVectorType::get requires │
│ an element type and an element count. Using ShuffleDstTy->getNumElements()    │
│ constructs the correct vector type for the compare cost, ensuring accurate    │
│ cost modeling. This prevents foldShuffleOfBinops from applying when it is not │
│ profitable or semantically safe. With correct cost evaluation, the transform  │
│ will no longer fire spuriously on the provided reproducer, avoiding the       │
│ incorrect zeroinitializer replacement.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe immediate bug   │
│ is the misuse of FixedVectorType::get in foldShuffleOfBinops, passing a type  │
│ where an element count is required. Fixing this to use                        │
│ ShuffleDstTy->getNumElements() will correct the cost computation for compare  │
│ folding, preventing the erroneous transformation observed in the reproducer.  │
│ Further auditing of icmp samesign handling can be done subsequently, but this │
│ fix addresses the identified first transformation and should resolve the      │
│ incorrect fold in this case."})                                               │
